@node Introduction "Introduction"

                                 @{b}Introduction@{ub}

   @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text}  is  a  little tool designed for adding icons to... Well, to almost
everything.  Using  this program you can create icon to any file, directory or
volume  (as  Disk.info  file). It's been written as a patch to well known file
manager  -  FileMaster, which in contrast to for example DirectoryOpus doesn't
support any option like this. Although this fact you can with no obstacles use
@{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text}  with  any  other  program  or simply use it as a normal CLI commmand.
@endnode

@node Instructions "Instructions"

                                 @{b}Instructions@{ub}

   First of all I'd like to explain how to use @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} installed in FileMaster
(instalation  is  described  in  node  @{"Instalation" link "Instalation"}). It's very simple. All you
have  to  do  is  enter  to  the  directory  you  want  and mark some files or
directories. Next, you should click on the "AddIcon" gadget. Small window will
be  opened and you will be asked to type an icon name. Write this name without
path  and '.info' append. If everything run OK after few moments you will have
your icons created.

   @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text}  is so inteligent program that reconizes icon type and checks if it
is  compatible to marked entry. It means that if you want to add icons to some
text  files  you  don't have to worry about marking by mistake (for example by
"Invert"  option) also directories. @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} will just omit them. Unfortunately
file type (Project/Tool) is not checked.

   Below the CLI/Shell template is described:

   @{b}AddIcon ICONFILE/A,ENTRY/A/M,ALL/S,QUIET/S@{ub}

 @{b}ICONFILE@{ub} @{i}(option required)@{ui}

It's  just  iconfile  name.  Must  be given, as I've written, without path and
'.info'  append. @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} will search for this file in one of three directories
in this order:

1) Program searches file AddIconPath in your ENV: assign. This file inludes a
   path to icons files stored on your hard disk. It is created during
   instalation but if you have installed this program yourself you have to
   create that file using any text editor. After successful locking the path
   @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} will try to read iconfile from that.
2) In case of failure in p.1) @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} will try to read icon from ENV:AddIcon/
   directory.
3) If even that fail a default icon will be readed if possible. Default icon
   is ENV:Sys/def_inonname.info

 @{b}ENTRY@{ub} @{i}(option required)@{ui}

Multiple strings option. This means you can give any number of entries. Just
type a list of files or directories you want @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} do add icons to. Note
that it's necesery to give first of them with full path.

 @{b}ALL@{ub} @{i}(switch - not required option)@{ui}

This switch informs program that you're going to add icons to all
files/directories existing in given directory. In this case only one ENTRY
option must be given and it must be a directory.

 @{b}QUIET@{ub} @{i}(switch - not required option)@{ui}

Do not print any messages. Sometimes it's very useful option but be awared
that you won't be informed if the program for any reasons fail.

   And now - some examples:

@{i}AddIcon txt df0:document@{ui}
A text file icon will be saved to a file 'document'

@{i}AddIcon pic dh2:Graphics/Pictures/Picture.iff girl.jpg landscape1.gif@{ui}
A picture icon will be saved to files mentioned above

@{i}AddIcon disk "Ram Disk:" df0: workbench: dh1:@{ui}
File 'Disk.info' will be saved on mentioned volumes

@{i}AddIcon drawer dh2:Modules/rock jazz disco metal news QUIET@{ui}
A few drawer icons will be created in directory dh2:Modules. You won't be
informed about any errors

@{i}AddIcon txt df0:Letters/ ALL@{ui}
Text file icons will be saved to all files in directory df0:Letters/
@endnode

@node Requirements "System requirements"

   Starting with version 2.0 @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} cannot be used under Kickstart 1.3 (on a
standard Amiga 500). For normal work @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} requires:

 - operating system 2.04+
 - icon.library (standard system library)
 - few dozen kilobytes of free memory.
 - set of icons stored in any directory

   This  program has been written 100% in assembler and compliled using AsmOne
1.29 under processor 68000. Source code has 9230 bytes.

@endnode

@node Errors "Error Messages"

                                @{b}Error messages@{ub}

   During work with @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} some error messages can appear:

   @{i}Error: Bad arguments!@{ui}
You didn't type one of required arguments.

   @{i}Error: Not enough memory for operation
Either you have very low memory or you're trying to add giganthic 256-colours
icon.

   @{i}Error: Icon file not found@{ui}
Icon file could not be found in any of three directories (you probably typed
wrong name).

   @{i}Error: Entry not found@{ui}
File or drawer does not exist.

   @{i}Error: Bad entry type@{ui}
Entry type does not match to icon type.

   @{i}Error: Could not open icon.library (any version)@{ui}
You should save icon.library to your Libs: directory.
@endnode

@node Instalation "Instalation"

                                 @{b}Instalation@{ub}

   @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} has been designed as a patch for FileMaster (it's been tested on FM
3.0 ß 2.1). Although this program can be used as a CLI command, using it under
FileMaster  is  much easier. To install @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} simpy doubleclick on 'Install'
icon and follow the installer messages. For all of you who would like to do it
yoursef I'll describe instalation step by step:

   a) copy @{fg shine}@{i}AddIcon@{ui}@{fg text} executable to C: assign
   b) copy any icons set to directory you've choosed
   c) launch any text editor and type full path to this directory, then save
      that file as ENVARC:AddIconPath; if you don't have any editor just
      type in CLI:
         Copy * TO ENVARC:AddIconPath
      then type path and  press CONTROL+'\'
   d) launch FileMaster, run configuration module, click 'Commands' and then
      click any unused gadget.
   e) set everything as follow:
      Priority:     Med
      Window:       Yes
      CD:           No Change
      Rescan:       Source
      Start Screen: No Change
      End Screen:   No Change
      Label:        AddIcon
      Pattern:      ---
      Offset:       0
      Signature:    ---
      Command:      C:AddIcon {r,IconName} {f} {O}
      Stack:        4000
      (where '---' menas that field must be clean)
   f) save configuration

   If  you  don't want to look at error messages (for example if you typed bad
icon  name  in  window) you can also set Window: No. It's possible to make any
changes  in  the set of icons (saving another icons, deleting them etc.) after
instalation.  It's  also  possible  to  change directory, where your icons are
stored. Just change path in file ENVARC:AddIconPath - that's all. 
@endnode

@node Future "What's in future"

                              @{b}What's in future?@{ub}

   I  hope  that's  final  version of this program, but if you send me any bug
raports I will try to fix the bugs as fast as possible. 
@endnode

